Kate Henshaw, the Nollywood actress, has taunted government-affiliated persons and prominent Nigerians who she suggested feign fainting in court.
On Monday, the wife of Abba Kyari, the suspended deputy commissioner of police (DCP), had fainted at the federal high court in Abuja.
She slumped shortly after Emeka Nwite, the trial judge, adjourned Kyari’s case for ruling on his bail application.
Henshaw said the “acting” was so good that she fears they might as well take the job from the actors.
“All these actors fainting upandan want collect work from our hand o,” she wrote via her Twitter handle on Monday.
ALSO READ: Abba Kyari’s ‘wife’ slumps in court
In another tweet, the film star added: “They faint They off-mic They are bedridden but not when they are stealing.”

All these actors fainting upandan want collect work from our hand o….

